SIMPLE: unlaid
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unlaid
<hw>Un*laid"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not laid
or placed; not fixed.</def> <rj><au>Hooker.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not allayed; not pacified; not laid finally to
rest.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Stubborn, <xex>unlaid</xex>
ghost.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not laid out, as a corpse.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Unlaid paper</b></col>. <cd>See <cref>Laid paper</cref>,
under <er>Laid</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unland</ent>⟦br⟧
